** The Role **

We're looking for an experienced IT professional with excellent communication
and organisation skills to join our team in a permanent capacity as a
Microsoft 365 Systems Engineer. The position will focus on the delivery of
projects using Microsoft 365 apps and services and Microsoft Azure and will
also require a good fundamental knowledge of general infrastructure. The role
is based in our Brisbane office and may require travel to client sites from
time to time.

** Responsibilities include: **

SME (Subject Matter Expert) for Microsoft 365 and OnPrem environments
including:

  * Hybrid cloud configuration, VM migration to Azure, and M365 management 
  * Active Directory and Azure AD expertise 
  * Intune / Endpoint Manager 
  * Exchange Online / Exchange OnPrem 
  * Sharepoint and OneDrive 
  * Teams 
  * B2B/B2C 
  * Security essentials such as IAM, DLP, M365 Compliance, Threat Management for Servers and Client OS 
  * Experience with Powershell and automation through 
    * Microsoft Graphs 
    * Power Automation 
    * Power BI 
  * Assisting service team with escalations from time to time 
  * Bachelor degree in Computer Science or relative work experience would be beneficial 

** Technical skills required: **

  * Microsoft 365 (Office 365) / Azure 
  * Intune 
  * Hypervisors 
  * Active directory 
  * Cisco networking desirable 

** Non-technical skills required: **

  * Great communication and documentation skills 
  * Solid organisation skills 
  * Can follow technical and work policies and maintain tracking information 
  * Proven time management and prioritization skills 
  * Excellent team player with the ability to work with stakeholders to plan and achieve goals. 

** About You **

We want to hear from you if you are looking for variety in your work and take
pride in delivering quality customer service. It is essential you are well
presented, have excellent communication skills and have the ability to talk
with senior members of a business in both a technical and non-technical style.

The ideal person for this role will have diverse experience with at least 3
years in a systems administration or systems engineering role.

You will work from our modern office building in a great team environment.
Along with this we also offer:

  * Attractive salary 
  * Full time permanent position with immediate start 
  * Industry training to help grow your technical knowledge 
  * Fantastic team of professionals with many years of experience and diverse industry qualifications 

